# Secure GitHub Push Plan

The goal is to push the project to GitHub without exposing any API keys, personal shopping data, or private information.

## Proposed Changes

### [requirements.txt](file:///d:/Project5/requirements.txt)
We will add `python-dotenv` to manage secrets via an environment file.
#### [MODIFY] [requirements.txt](file:///d:/Project5/requirements.txt)

### [telegram_utils.py](file:///d:/Project5/telegram_utils.py)
We will modify the file to read the `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` and `TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID` from environment variables rather than hardcoding them.
#### [MODIFY] [telegram_utils.py](file:///d:/Project5/telegram_utils.py)

### `.gitignore`
We will create a `.gitignore` file to ensure the following are not tracked by version control:
- `.env` (API keys and secrets)
- `*.db`, `*.sqlite3` (SQLite databases containing private records)
- `*.json` (JSON dumps containing user history and preferences)
- `__pycache__/` and `*.pyc` (Python artifacts)
- `tmp/`, `archive/`
#### [NEW] [.gitignore](file:///d:/Project5/.gitignore)

